gnificant milestone in Goldberg's design evolution as it indicates his first attempt at working with non-rectilinear spaces. Though aesthetically box-like, the Unicel is structurally a tube, which is \"simply a cylinder lying [sic] on its side.\"","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_002234.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":"26.275390625","resource_grade_level":"","resource_curriculum":"","resource_tour":"","resource_file_time":"00m 00s","resource_file_time_unformatted":"0","resource_source_detail":"\"Architecture for Urbanism: Selections from the Bertrand Goldberg Archive,\" Case 2, Ryerson &amp; Burnham Libraries, November 1, 2011\u2013January 2, 2012<br \/>\n<br \/>\n<a href=&quot;http:\/\/digital-libraries.saic.edu\/u?\/mqc,14886&quot;>Link to R&amp;B Archives Digital Collections record<\/a>","resource_tags_for_resource_id":"Chicago, trains"},"resource_2235":{"resource_link":"..\/2235","resource_url":"http:\/\/www.artic.edu\/aic\/collections\/citi\/resources\/Rsrc_002235.jpg","resource_title":"06. Pressed Steel Car Company, Unicel Freight Cars. Exterior view, c.1950-1951.","resource_description":"Hegewisch, Chicago, IL, 1950-51. Hedrich-Blessing, photographer.","resource_full_text":"","resource_types_for_resource_id":"Archival Material","resource_asset_type":"10","resource_image_thumbnail":"..\/images\/Rsrc_TN_002235.jpg","resource_asset_type_label":"","resource_file_size":"0.0 kB","resource_file_size_unformatted":"62.212890625","resource_grade_level":"","resource_curriculum":"","resource_tour":"","resource_file_time":"00m 00s","resource_file_time_unformatted":"0","resource_source_detail":"\"Architecture for Urbanism: Selections from the Bertrand Goldberg Archive,\" Case 2, Ryerson &amp; Burnham Libraries, November 1, 2011\u2013January 2, 2012","resource_tags_for_resource_id":"Chicago,